e with other people, ok?</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Ok, Buddy. Will do.</span>','Conversation with Captain America/Drake','','inherit','open','open','','317-revision-v1','','','2014-06-23 07:58:42','2014-06-23 14:58:42','',317,'http://conversationswithdrake.com/2014/06/23/317-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(319,1,'2014-06-23 07:59:57','2014-06-23 14:59:57','<span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me, <em>while pouring a bowl of cereal:</em></strong> Do you want milk in this, Cap?</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake, in a whisper:</strong> Mommy, it\'s me. It\'s Drake!</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Drake! You aren\'t Captain America anymore? </span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> No, Mommy. I\'m still Cap, too. But I\'m always your Drake Buddy.</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Ok. </span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Ok. But Mommy, just call me Cap when we are with other people, ok?</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Ok, Buddy. Will do.</span>','Conversation with Captain America/Drake','','inherit','open','open','','317-revision-v1','','','2014-06-23 07:59:57','2014-06-23 14:59:57','',317,'http://conversationswithdrake.com/2014/06/23/317-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(321,1,'2014-06-29 18:55:12','2014-06-30 01:55:12','<span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Hey, dude!</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Mommy, do NOT call me \"Dude.\" Just call me Drake or Cap!</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Okay, Cap. Sorry.</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> It\'s ok. Just don\'t call me Dude. Because Dude is just my MIDDLE name.</span>','Hey dude','','publish','open','open','','hey-dude','','','2014-06-29 18:55:12','2014-06-30 01:55:12','',0,'http://conversationswithdrake.com/?p=321',0,'post','',0),(322,1,'2014-06-29 18:55:12','2014-06-30 01:55:12','<span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Hey, dude!</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Mommy, do NOT call me \"Dude.\" Just call me Drake or Cap!</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Okay, Cap. Sorry.</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> It\'s ok. Just don\'t call me Dude. Because Dude is just my MIDDLE name.</span>','Hey dude','','inherit','open','open','','321-revision-v1','','','2014-06-29 18:55:12','2014-06-30 01:55:12','',321,'http://conversationswithdrake.com/2014/06/29/321-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(324,2,'2014-07-01 22:09:39','2014-07-02 05:09:39','<em><span style=\"color: #141823;\">Conversation with Drake, when I wimped out and made pancakes for dinner after a long day, instead of the more delicious/nutritious/work intensive meal I had planned:</span></em><br style=\"color: #141823;\" /><span style=\"color: #141823;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Drake, come and eat!</span><br style=\"color: #141823;\" /><span style=\"color: #141823;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> It\'s pancakes! Whew! What a relief (which he pronounced \"WeeWeef\")!</span><br style=\"color: #141823;\" /><span style=\"color: #141823;\"><strong>Me:</strong> You like pancakes best, Cap?</span><br style=\"color: #141823;\" /><span style=\"color: #141823;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Yeah. Because some other dinners are just too YUCKY!</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\" style=\"color: #141823;\">\r\n<strong>Me:</strong> Hey, Drake! That\'s not nice to say. Besides, Daddy likes my dinners.\r\n<strong>Drake, <em>after a long pause:</em></strong> Mommy...I think Daddy is not telling you the truth.</span>','Pancakes','','publish','open','open','','pancakes','','','2014-07-01 22:09:39','2014-07-02 05:09:39','',0,'http://conversationswithdrake.com/?p=324',0,'post','',0),(325,2,'2014-07-01 22:09:39','2014-07-02 05:09:39','<em><span style=\"color: #141823;\">Conversation with Drake, when I wimped out and made pancakes for dinner after a long day, instead of the more delicious/nutritious/work intensive meal I had planned:</span></em><br style=\"color: #141823;\" /><span style=\"color: #141823;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Drake, come and eat!</span><br style=\"color: #141823;\" /><span style=\"color: #141823;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> It\'s pancakes! Whew! What a relief (which he pronounced \"WeeWeef\")!</span><br style=\"color: #141823;\" /><span style=\"color: #141823;\"><strong>Me:</strong> You like pancakes best, Cap?</span><br style=\"color: #141823;\" /><span style=\"color: #141823;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Yeah. Because some other dinners are just too YUCKY!</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\" style=\"color: #141823;\">\r\n<strong>Me:</strong> Hey, Drake! That\'s not nice to say. Besides, Daddy likes my dinners.\r\n<strong>Drake, <em>after a long pause:</em></strong> Mommy...I think Daddy is not telling you the truth.</span>','Pancakes','','inherit','open','open','','324-revision-v1','','','2014-07-01 22:09:39','2014-07-02 05:09:39','',324,'http://conversationswithdrake.com/2014/07/01/324-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(326,2,'2014-07-02 20:33:16','2014-07-03 03:33:16','<em><span style=\"color: #141823;\">Conversation with Drake, during our nightly chat about the things he did well today:</span></em><br style=\"color: #141823;\" /><span style=\"color: #141823;\"><strong>Me:</strong> You were a pretty great swimmer today, Drake! You are learning new things!</span><br style=\"color: #141823;\" /><span style=\"color: #141823;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Thanks, Mom! You were a pretty good time-outer today!</span><br style=\"color: #141823;\" /><span style=\"color: #141823;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Um...thanks, Drake.</span>','The time-outer','','publish','open','open','','the-time-outer','','','2014-07-02 20:33:16','2014-07-03 03:33:16','',0,'http://conversationswithdrake.com/?p=326',0,'post','',0),(327,2,'2014-07-02 20:33:16','2014-07-03 03:33:16','<em><span style=\"color: #141823;\">Conversation with Drake, during our nightly chat about the things he did well today:</span></em><br style=\"color: #141823;\" /><span style=\"color: #141823;\"><strong>Me:</strong> You were a pretty great swimmer today, Drake! You are learning new things!</span><br style=\"color: #141823;\" /><span style=\"color: #141823;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Thanks, Mom! You were a pretty good time-outer today!</span><br style=\"color: #141823;\" /><span style=\"color: #141823;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Um...thanks, Drake.</span>','The time-outer','','inherit','open','open','','326-revision-v1','','','2014-07-02 20:33:16','2014-07-03 03:33:16','',326,'http://conversationswithdrake.com/2014/07/02/326-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(329,1,'2014-07-20 13:49:12','2014-07-20 20:49:12','<span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Mom, in Charlie and the Chocolate Factory, there\'s only five tickets ever in the world.</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Yes, Drake. Just five tickets.</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Why didn\'t they make more tickets? Everyone wanted more!</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Mr. Wonka only wanted to let in a few children to his factory.</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Mom! Mom! What we should do is, we should get some gold ticket papers and we should make MORE tickets and sell them! And we make people so happy and we get money for toys!</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Drake, I think that\'s forgery.</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Yeah! Let\'s forgery!</span>','Criminal Mastermind','','publish','open','open','','criminal-mastermind','','','2014-07-23 13:50:15','2014-07-23 20:50:15','',0,'http://conversationswithdrake.com/?p=329',0,'post','',0),(330,1,'2014-07-23 13:50:15','2014-07-23 20:50:15','<span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Mom, in Charlie and the Chocolate Factory, there\'s only five tickets ever in the world.</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Yes, Drake. Just five tickets.</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Why didn\'t they make more tickets? Everyone wanted more!</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Mr. Wonka only wanted to let in a few children to his factory.</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Mom! Mom! What we should do is, we should get some gold ticket papers and we should make MORE tickets and sell them! And we make people so happy and we get money for toys!</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Drake, I think that\'s forgery.</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Yeah! Let\'s forgery!</span>','Criminal Mastermind','','inherit','open','open','','329-revision-v1','','','2014-07-23 13:50:15','2014-07-23 20:50:15','',329,'http://conversationswithdrake.com/2014/07/23/329-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(331,1,'2014-07-19 13:51:11','2014-07-19 20:51:11','<span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake, <em>as Captain America, in a menacing voice</em>:</strong> Hulk, I\'m gonna GET you!</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> I thought Cap and Hulk were friends! Why are they fighting?</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake,<em> rolling his eyes</em>:</strong> These are just TOYS, Mom. It\'s ok.</span>','They are just TOYS','','publish','open','open','','they-are-just-toys','','','2014-07-23 13:51:22','2014-07-23 20:51:22','',0,'http://conversationswithdrake.com/?p=331',0,'post','',0),(332,1,'2014-07-23 13:51:11','2014-07-23 20:51:11','<span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake, <em>as Captain America, in a menacing voice</em>:</strong> Hulk, I\'m gonna GET you!</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> I thought Cap and Hulk were friends! Why are they fighting?</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake,<em> rolling his eyes</em>:</strong> These are just TOYS, Mom. It\'s ok.</span>','They are just TOYS','','inherit','open','open','','331-revision-v1','','','2014-07-23 13:51:11','2014-07-23 20:51:11','',331,'http://conversationswithdrake.com/2014/07/23/331-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(333,1,'2014-07-10 13:52:00','2014-07-10 20:52:00','<span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Mom, I fell down! </span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Oh, no! Are you going to be ok?</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> yeah.</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> I\'m so sorry you fell, Buddy.</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake, <em>sighing deeply</em>:</strong> Well, Mom, life isn\'t just rainbows around every corner, you know.</span>','Rainbows around every corner','','publish','open','open','','rainbows-around-every-corner','','','2014-07-23 13:52:52','2014-07-23 20:52:52','',0,'http://conversationswithdrake.com/?p=333',0,'post','',0),(334,1,'2014-07-23 13:52:52','2014-07-23 20:52:52','<span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> Mom, I fell down! </span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> Oh, no! Are you going to be ok?</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake:</strong> yeah.</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Me:</strong> I\'m so sorry you fell, Buddy.</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake, <em>sighing deeply</em>:</strong> Well, Mom, life isn\'t just rainbows around every corner, you know.</span>','Rainbows around every corner','','inherit','open','open','','333-revision-v1','','','2014-07-23 13:52:52','2014-07-23 20:52:52','',333,'http://conversationswithdrake.com/2014/07/23/333-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(335,1,'2014-07-23 13:53:55','2014-07-23 20:53:55','<em><span style=\"color: #37404e;\">Whilst dropping him at school this morning:</span></em><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\">**We arrive and two little girls rush over to Drake to hug him**</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Zoey:</strong> Caitlin, NO! That\'s MY DRAKE!!</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Caitlin, <em>sadly</em>:</strong> But I wanted to play with Drake today!!</span><br style=\"color: #37404e;\" /><span style=\"color: #37404e;\"><strong>Drake<em> (putting a hand on each girl\'s shoulder)</em>:</strong> Girls, it\'s ok. You can share me.</span>','Ladie\'s Man','','publish','open','open','','ladies-man','','','2014-07-23 13:53:55','2014-07-23 20:53:55','',0,'http://conversationswithdrake.com/?p=335',0,'post','',0),(336,1,'2014-07-23 13:53:55','2014-07-23 20:53:55','<em><span style=\"color: #